<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> And as I stated the effects of iksar regeneration rates on necromantic mana regeneration are pretty DEEP in that class/race combonations mechanics and something I'm more than happy to state I was ignorant of in the first place because, as I stated, I don't play necromancers, I play a cleric<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I don't really think it is that DEEP in the mechanics... I don't really think it takes a DEEP thinking person to realise that:<br>
<br>
(1) Lich takes HP and gives you mana<br>
(2) Iksar innate regen GIVES you HP<br>
(3) (1) + (2) = more mana with less HP lost...<br>
<br>
I really don't see that as a difficult thing around which to wrap ones mind.<br>
<br>
Or:  if you would prefer it in &quot;cleric&quot; terms:<br>
<br>
I don't eat as many HP to get back the same amount of mana with which to pump you and cast various spells.  IE:  You don't have to heal me as often (if I am a tool and don't lifetap -- which I am).<br>
<br>
Just an oberservation -- Or my opinion on the matters being debated, if you will.<br>
<br>
Thanks!<br>
<br>
